# Zoo LinkedList

A singly linked list implementation that manages Animal objects in Java.

## What it does

Manages a zoo of animals using a custom linked list.
Supports adding animals, duplicating the list, filtering by category,
and simulating a feeding queue that processes animals one at a time.

## Concepts covered

- Enums (Category, Diet)
- Classes and constructors
- Singly linked list (AddHead, AddTail, RemoveHead)
- Object composition
- Method overloading
- Category filtering with duplicate()